'''Fiat-Allis''' (1974 to 1985), later renamed '''Fiatallis''' (1985 to early 1990s), was a [[brand]] of [[heavy equipment]] (also called construction equipment, earthmoving equipment, or engineering vehicles), such as [[loader (equipment)|loaders]], [[bulldozer]]s, [[backhoe]]s, [[wheel tractor-scraper|scrapers]], and [[grader]]s. It began in 1974, when [[Allis-Chalmers]]'s construction equipment business was reorganized into a [[joint venture]] with [[Fiat|Fiat SpA]],<ref name="Buescher1991p316">{{Harvnb|Buescher|1991|p=316}}.</ref><ref name="Dean2001p134">{{Harvnb|Dean|2001|p=134}}.</ref> which bought a 65% majority stake at the outset.<ref name="Dean2001p134"/> 

Allis-Chalmers's construction equipment business was often not profitable during the 1950s and 1960s. It faced stiff competition from companies such as [[Caterpillar Inc.|Caterpillar]], [[Case Corporation|Case]], [[Euclid Trucks|Euclid]], [[John Deere]], [[Fiat Trattori|Fiat MMT]], and others. The 1974 formation of a new company, Fiat-Allis, was essentially a [[divestment]]. 

Over the next decade, Fiat continued to invest in Fiat-Allis, more so than Allis-Chalmers did. The two parent firms disagreed on decisions made at, and about, Fiat-Allis. In 1985, the joint venture ended. Fiat bought out Allis's remaining minority stake (which had shrunk from its original 35%). Fiat renamed the company Fiatallis.<ref name="Haycraft2000p278">{{Harvnb|Haycraft|2000|p=278}}.</ref> 

[[File:Fiat Hitachi FH240LC.3 p2.JPG|thumb|Fiat-Hitachi FH240LC [[excavator|trackhoe]].]]

Cooperation with [[Hitachi]] yielded '''Fiat-Hitachi''' branding for some years. Fiatallis was eventually sold to [[CNH (company)|CNH]], of which Fiat is a major stockholder. CNH retired the Fiatallis brand and merged the company's assets with others from [[Case Corporation|Case]] and [[New Holland Machine Company]]. CNH's construction equipment line is called [[New Holland Construction]]. 

In Argentina, Fiat-Allis was produced by Crybsa. This product under license 605-B excavator<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pesadosargentinos.blogspot.com.ar/2015/07/crybsa-605-b.html|title=Pesados Argentinos: Crybsa 605-B|first=Esteban|last=Dl|date=23 July 2015|publisher=}}</ref>, C-130<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pesadosargentinos.blogspot.com.ar/2015/01/crybsa-c-130.html|title=Pesados Argentinos: Crybsa C-130|first=Esteban|last=Dl|date=23 July 2015|publisher=}}</ref> and crawler tractor 7D<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pesadosargentinos.blogspot.com.ar/2014/11/crybsa-7-d.html|title=Pesados Argentinos: Crybsa 7-D|first=Esteban|last=Dl|date=27 March 2015|publisher=}}</ref>.

